<br>
Scripted events indicate things that may, or may not require an empty zone (other than the participants, mind you). <br>
<br>
A good example of this would be the RZtW scripted event, that turns the zone he is in, from a decent XP spot, to a murderous death hole for the unprepared player. <br>
<br>
I used the example that hate has no zone wide scripts to support removing it from the reservations system, and not inversely to suggest that all scripted events should have a place on the calandar... those scripted events with rotation properties are already, by and large, on rotation. The ones that are not on rotation are actually written down with regards to the ettiquitte for the zone and the encounter. <br>
<br>
If it did have a zone wide scripted event that could be interupted or ruined by someone acting contrary to the script, that would support, not detract, from the use of a calandard system. However, due, as has been said, to the repop times being a variable, the rotation system is better suited than the calandar system to portioning out when the scripted event is due, and for whom. <br>
<br>
